image.altText: A close up shot of a brown and tan dachshund / sausage dog, with big eyes looking directly into camera.

props.synopsis:
A dachshund who became stuck in a rabbit hole in the Central Australian town of Yulara has been rescued over the weekend.

The rescue effort, which took six hours, rallied the community, with a local plumber and NT Fire and Rescue Service members providing vital help.

Alice the dachshund's minders say she has recovered from the shock and seems undeterred from chasing rabbits.

title.children: Alice the dachshund rescued after six hours stuck down rabbit hole
